<problem>
<variantControl nVariants='1' />
<title>Linear approximation of quadratic</title>

<setup>

<function name='f' variables='x' symbolic>x^2</function>
<function name='fprime' variables='x' symbolic>2x</function>
<function name='L_general' symbolic variables='a x' >$$fprime(a) * (x-a) + $$f(a)</function>

<math name='x1'>2</math>
<function name='L1' variables='x' >$$fprime($x1 )*(x-$x1 )+$$f($x1 )</function>

<math name='x2'>-1</math>
<function name='L2' variables='x' >$$fprime($x2 )*(x-$x2 )+$$f($x2 )</function>

<evaluate name='fx1' function="$f" input="$x1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='fprimex1' function="$fprime" input="$x1" forceNumeric />
  
<evaluate name='f_1' function="$f" input="1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L1_1' function="$L1" input="1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_2' function="$f" input="2" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L1_2' function="$L1" input="2" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_19' function="$f" input="1.9" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L1_19' function="$L1" input="1.9" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_21' function="$f" input="2.1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L1_21' function="$L1" input="2.1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_10' function="$f" input="10" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L1_10' function="$L1" input="10" forceNumeric />

<math name='L1closelist'  unordered='true'>2,1.9,2.1</math>
<math name='L1farlist'  unordered='true'>1,10</math>


<evaluate name='f_n2' function="$f" input="-2" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_n1' function="$f" input="-1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_n11' function="$f" input="-1.1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='f_n09' function="$f" input="-0.9" forceNumeric />
  
<evaluate name='L2_n2' function="$L2" input="-2" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L2_n1' function="$L2" input="-1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L2_n11' function="$L2" input="-1.1" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L2_n09' function="$L2" input="-0.9" forceNumeric />
<evaluate name='L2_10' function="$L2" input="10" forceNumeric />
  
<math name='L2closelist'  unordered='true'>-1,-1.1,-0.9</math>
<math name='L2farlist'  unordered='true'>-2,10</math>

</setup>


<p>Let <m>f(x)= $f</m>.  We will calculate linear approximations of <m>f</m> around different points.   But first, sketch the graph of <m>f</m> below. Drag the three <copy prop='styleDescription' tname="pf1" /> points so that the <copy prop='styleDescription' tname="myParab" /> curve is the graph of <m>f</m>.
</p>


<graph width='500' height='300' xmin='-5' xmax='5' ymin='-2' ymax='5'  showNavigation='false'>

<parabola hide fixed name='parab' through='(0, $$f(0)) (1, $$f(1)) (-1, $$f(-1))'/>

<point name='pf1' x='-1' y='0'>
<constraints>
<attractTo>$parab</attractTo><attractTo><point>(0,0)</point></attractTo>
</constraints>
</point>

<point name='pf2' x='1' y='0'>
<constraints>
<attractTo>$parab</attractTo><attractTo><point>(0,0)</point></attractTo>
</constraints>
</point>

<point name='pf3' x='2' y='0'>
<constraints>
<attractTo>$parab</attractTo><attractTo><point>(0,0)</point></attractTo>
</constraints>
</point>

<parabola name='myParab' through='$pf1 $pf2 $pf3' />

</graph>

<answer>
<award><when>
$$f(  $(pf1{prop='x'})  ) = $(pf1{prop='y'}) and
$$f(  $(pf2{prop='x'})  ) = $(pf2{prop='y'}) and
$$f(  $(pf3{prop='x'})  ) = $(pf3{prop='y'})
</when></award>
</answer>



