</answer>


<p>The linear approximation (or tangent line) to <m>f</m> around <m>x=$x1 </m> is a line through the point <m>($x1 ,f($x1 ))</m> with slope <m>f'($x1 )</m>:  <me>y=f'($x1 )(x-$x1 ) + f($x1 ).</me>  Write the equation for this linear approximation.
</p>
  
<p>
<m>y=</m> 
