<point stylenumber='3' fixed>(0,-1)</point>
<copy stylenumber='3' tname='L2' />

</graph>


<ol>

<li>
<m>f'(x)=<copy prop="formula" tname="fprime" /></m>

<p><m>f($x1 )=$fx1 </m>, <m>f'($x1 )=$fprimex1 </m>.  <m>y=$fprimex1 (x-$x1 )+$fx1 </m>, which you could also write as <m>y=<copy prop="formula" tname="L1" /></m>.</p>

</li>

<li>
<p>
<m>L_{ $x1  }(x)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$fprimex1 </number></round>(x-$x1 )+<round numberdigits="4"><number>$fx1 </number></round></m>, which you could also write as <m>L_{ $x1  }(x)=<copy prop="formula" tname="L1" /></m>.</p>

<p><m>f(1)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_1 </number></round></m>. <m>L_{ $x1  }(1)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$L1_1 </number></round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(2)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_2 </number></round></m>, <m>L_{ $x1  }(2)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$L1_2 </number></round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(1.9) = <round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_19 </number></round></m>, <m>L_{ $x1  }(1.9) = <round numberdigits="4"><number>$L1_19 </number></round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(2.1) = <round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_21 </number></round></m>, <m>L_{ $x1  }(2.1)= <round numberdigits="4"><number>$L1_21 </number></round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(10)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_10 </number></round></m>, <m>L_{ $x1  }(10) = <round numberdigits="4"><number>$L1_10 </number></round></m></p>

<p><m>L_{ $x1  }(x)</m> is close to <m>f(x)</m> when <m>x</m> is close to $x1 , so for the values <m>x=$L1closelist </m>.  It is a bad approximation to <m>f(x)</m> when <m>x</m> is far from $x1 , so for the values <m>x=$L1farlist </m>.</p>
</li>

<li>
<p><m>f(-1)=1</m>, <m>f'(-1)=-2</m></p>

<p><m>y=-2(x+1)+1</m> or <m>y=-2x-1</m></p>

<p><m>L_{ $x2  }(x)=-2(x+1)+1</m> or <m>L_{ $x2  }(x)=-2x-1</m></p>

<p><m>f(-2)=<round numberdecimals="4">$f_n2 </round></m>, <m>L_{ $x2  }(-2)=<round numberdecimals="4">$L2_n2 </round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(-1)=<round numberdecimals="4">$f_n1 </round></m>, <m>L_{ $x2  }(-1)=<round numberdecimals="4">$L2_n1 </round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(-1.1)=<round numberdecimals="4">$f_n11 </round></m>, <m>L_{ $x2  }(-1.1) = <round numberdecimals="4">$L2_n11 </round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(-0.9)=<round numberdecimals="4">$f_n09 </round></m>, <m>L_{ $x2  }(-0.9) =<round numberdecimals="4">$L2_n09 </round></m>
</p>
<p>

<m>f(10)=<round numberdigits="4"><number>$f_10 </number></round></m>, <m>L_{ $x2  }(10)=<round numberdecimals="4">$L2_10 </round></m></p>

<p><m>L(x)</m> is close to <m>f(x)</m> when <m>x</m> is close to -1, so for the values <m>x=$L2closelist </m>.  It is a bad approximation to <m>f(x)</m> when <m>x</m> is far from -1, so for the values <m>x=$L2farlist </m>.</p>

</li>


</ol>

</solution>


